    <summary>03/17/1993: Spanish priest Bernardo Blanco was abducted at gunpoint by members of the Abu Sayyaf Group (ASG) while driving in a rural area of the island of Basilan in the Philippines. The Group demanded 14 million Philippine pesos (approximately $500,000) in ransom. On May 3, 1993, a Philippine military rescue operation began, which resulted in the death of 41 members of the terrorist group. Blanco escaped on May 4th, stealing away while his captors were asleep.</summary>
